headline.main: ASSASSINS IN IRAQ KILL ARAB LEADER; Fakhri Bey Nashashibi, Foe of Terrorists in Palestine, Slain in Baghdad BACKED BRITISH IN WAR Victim Denounced Haj Amin el Husseini, Now in Berlin, After Flight From Country

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 9 (AP) -- Reuter reported from Baghdad today that Fakhri Bey Nashashibi, a leading Palestine Arab, had been assassinated as he was leaving his hotel in the Iraq city. He was among the leading Arab supporters of the British cause in the war.
abstract: Slain by pro-Axis factions in Iraq; career revd; por
